      "content": "thanks. u mentioned the \"potential for improved market reputation\" but for a lot of these guys, it feels like a huge stretch. don't you think the actual, immediate cost of the equipment and the compliance paperwork is a much more certain threat to their survival than some vague benefit like \"reputation\" or \"innovation\"?",
